; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures I2C module as a master and receives data via I2C.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Connecting ports with an external I2C device should be correct.
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. I2C
;    2. PCU/GPIO
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. I2C0    : PB8 (Serial Clock)
;               : PB9 (Serial Data)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; I2C0
; 1. Channel                   : 0 (I2C0)
;
; 2. Config                    : [ 0 i m 400000 ]
;    Operation                 : i (Interrupt)
;    Mode                      : m (Master)
;    Baudrate                  : 400000 (400KHz)
;
; 3. Rx                        : [ 0 8 -saddr 0x49 ]
;    Receive Data Length       : 8
;    Slave Address             : 0x49 (Hexa Format)
;
; PCU (I2C0)
; 1. Port Group                : 1 (PCU Port B)
;
; 2. Port                      : [ 1 8 a 1 -pupd p ] [ 1 9 a 1 -pupd p ]
;    Pin Number                : 8 / 9 
;    Pin Mode                  : a (Alternative)
;    Alternative               : 1 (SCL/SDA)
;    Pull-up/down              : p (Pull-up)
;
; PCU
sendln 'cm pcu'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 1 8 a 1 -pupd p'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 1 9 a 1 -pupd p'
mpause 30

; I2C0
sendln 'cm i2c'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 0 i m 400000'
mpause 30
sendln 'rx 0 8 -saddr 0x49'
